\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
6.
 Policy Statement
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Elko County requires a governance structure that connects strategic direction from County leadership to the technical execution of Information Operations.
 This policy establishes the formal authority designations,
 interdepartmental boundaries,
 and escalation constructs that ensure IT decisions are made at the appropriate level,
 funded through proper channels,
 and overseen with accountability.
 This policy defines the governance structure within which the delegation framework established in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.08"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 operates;
 it does not create or modify delegation records,
 stand-in authority,
 or exception approval mechanisms.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.1 Delegated Governance Framework
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Elko County hereby establishes a delegated governance model for IT oversight.
 Strategic direction and budget appropriation are established by the Board of County Commissioners under NRS 244.
 The execution of technical strategy is delegated to the Information Operations Department in accordance with the decision rights defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.08"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Program Leadership
\series default
:
 The IT Director shall serve as the designated senior official with responsibility and authority to coordinate,
 develop,
 implement,
 and maintain the County's information security program,
 consistent with NIST SP 800-53 Rev.
 5:
 PM-2 (Information Security Program Leadership).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Central Authority
\series default
:
 The Information Operations Department is designated as the sole authoritative source for all IT-related governance policy,
 technical standards,
 and architecture coordination across County departments.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Operational Independence
\series default
:
 The Information Operations Department shall operate with the autonomy required to enforce compliance standards,
 as defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.03"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Standard Operating Ethos).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.2 Policy and Enforcement Authority
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The IT Director holds the delegated authority to develop IT policy,
 enforce technical standards,
 and manage operational decisions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Binding Nature
\series default
:
 The Information Operations Department shall enforce all formally adopted IT policies and technical standards across all Elko County departments,
 systems,
 and personnel.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
CJIS Management Control
\series default
:
 Consistent with CJIS Security Policy v6.0:
 Section 5.1.1.4 (Management Control Agreements) and applicable Management Control Agreements,
 the Criminal Justice Agency (CJA) retains management control over criminal justice functions and Criminal Justice Information (CJI).
 Within that framework,
 the IT Director (as LASO),
 acting as the CJA's technical agent,
 shall exercise exclusive administrative control over the configuration,
 security,
 and management of hardware,
 software,
 and firmware that transmit or store CJI on County-managed infrastructure,
 regardless of the user department.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.3 Access and Change Governance
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The IT Director shall reserve the following decision rights exclusively for Information Operations leadership to maintain the integrity of the County network.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Access Control
\series default
:
 The IT Director shall retain operational authority over the granting,
 modification,
 and revocation of logical access privileges to County information systems and physical access to IT-controlled facilities (e.g.,
 data centers,
 server rooms,
 network closets),
 implemented in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:2.04"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Access Control Policy) and 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:2.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Personnel Security and Background Screening Policy).
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Constraint
\series default
:
 For systems processing CJI,
 the IT Director shall ensure that access decisions comply with the CJIS Security Policy and applicable Management Control Agreements.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Change Control
